Key Match Events: Jamal Musiala scored the opening goal in the 22nd minute.
Ilkay Gündoğan scored Germany's second goal in the second half.
Manuel Neuer made a crucial save from Dominik Szoboszlai's free kick.
Post-Match Reflections: Germany coach Julian Nagelsmann praised Jamal Musiala's performance and his ability to handle pressure.
Hungary coach Marco Rossi criticized the referee's performance, claiming unbalanced refereeing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Hungary almost took the lead within the first 20 seconds of the match.
Germany's victory secured their spot in the Euro 2024 knockout stage.
Hungary's unbeaten streak against Germany ended with this match.
